00:45:11,863 --> 00:45:14,585
Once you've heard it the first time,

774
00:45:15,666 --> 00:45:17,547
the persistent bool will become true.

775
00:45:17,967 --> 00:45:19,908
And this is across all playthroughs.

776
00:45:20,108 --> 00:45:22,810
So when you go back, he will definitely have that phone.

777
00:45:23,210 --> 00:45:24,791
We also use this for all of the reveals.

778
00:45:25,552 --> 00:45:27,873
So if you've heard it once, you never have to reveal it again.

779
00:45:28,614 --> 00:45:30,555
You can still go over and listen to them,

780
00:45:30,655 --> 00:45:32,497
and the widget will show up and all that stuff,

781
00:45:33,518 --> 00:45:35,900
because we wanted players to feel that consistency

782
00:45:35,940 --> 00:45:37,021
in the HUD design as well.

783
00:45:37,862 --> 00:45:38,562
But you don't have to.

784
00:45:38,862 --> 00:45:41,004
You can just skip that step and go right ahead.

785
00:45:42,506 --> 00:45:44,307
And we added an Intel HUD message.

786
00:45:44,387 --> 00:45:46,629
We had Intel along, but it wasn't very prominent.

787
00:45:47,510 --> 00:45:49,592
So we decided to push it a little bit

788
00:45:49,772 --> 00:45:52,014
to make sure that players felt like they had that option as

789
00:45:52,034 --> 00:45:53,916
well, instead of just using opportunities.

790
00:45:54,156 --> 00:45:55,677
I'll show you an example in a second.

791
00:45:57,327 --> 00:45:59,488
And then we added different levels of guidance.

792
00:46:00,708 --> 00:46:02,989
So you can decide if you want full opportunities,

793
00:46:03,350 --> 00:46:08,172
if you want to have this minimal version where we don't give you

794
00:46:08,392 --> 00:46:11,233
the marker in the world, but only the objective.

795
00:46:11,714 --> 00:46:13,935
And it's up for you to find out how you want to do it.

796
00:46:16,814 --> 00:46:18,916
Yes, and this is an example of Intel.

797
00:46:18,956 --> 00:46:20,097
This is Fireworks Schedule.

798
00:46:20,818 --> 00:46:26,302
You read it, view Intel, take you to the menu, and here you have a description.

799
00:46:26,342 --> 00:46:30,565
These are kind of all the little parts of the opportunities, and if you are that type

800
00:46:30,605 --> 00:46:36,030
of player who just wants to investigate on your own, we encourage you to use this instead.

801
00:46:37,571 --> 00:46:38,452
The compromise, yes.

802
00:46:40,346 --> 00:46:43,132
I call this a compromise and not the perfect solution,

803
00:46:44,014 --> 00:46:45,878
because it really is a compromise,

804
00:46:45,978 --> 00:46:47,943
and it's something that we keep adjusting.

805
00:46:51,447 --> 00:46:52,848
what is the most important part?

806
00:46:53,008 --> 00:46:55,170
Is it the sandbox, or is it the guidance?

807
00:46:55,671 --> 00:46:57,332
And we also have replay value on top of that.

808
00:46:58,353 --> 00:47:00,616
So, fancy.

809
00:47:01,757 --> 00:47:03,519
So this is something that you constantly

810
00:47:03,559 --> 00:47:06,622
have to adjust, because there's always

811
00:47:07,322 --> 00:47:10,025
some really, really cool idea about some narrative part that

812
00:47:10,065 --> 00:47:10,926
would be great to do.

813
00:47:10,986 --> 00:47:12,327
And then you have to think about, well,

814
00:47:12,367 --> 00:47:13,568
what would that do to sandbox?

815
00:47:13,588 --> 00:47:15,270
And then what would that do to replay value?

816
00:47:16,231 --> 00:47:17,792
And this is something that we do all the time.

817
00:47:18,212 --> 00:47:19,954
It's not that we made up our minds and then we said,

818
00:47:19,994 --> 00:47:22,275
go, everyone, this is a template, design, design.

819
00:47:23,876 --> 00:47:25,818
Every time we have a new opportunity idea,

820
00:47:25,838 --> 00:47:27,199
we sit and we talk about this.

821
00:47:27,819 --> 00:47:29,740
Every time we add a step to an opportunity,

822
00:47:29,801 --> 00:47:30,601
we talk about this.

823
00:47:31,482 --> 00:47:33,843
This is a constant readjusting,

824
00:47:34,824 --> 00:47:36,365
and it's something that we're still working with,

825
00:47:36,806 --> 00:47:38,207
thanks to our episodic model.

826
00:47:39,067 --> 00:47:40,348
We can keep adjusting this.

827
00:47:41,949 --> 00:47:42,249
So, yes.

828
00:47:43,647 --> 00:47:46,428
So we managed to show them the iceberg

829
00:47:46,708 --> 00:47:50,089
and still encourage replay in a balance

